commitResults.messageTitle: Skeletal version of Duke
Add the ability to store text entered by the user
Add the ability to mark tasks as done and change the status back to not done.
Add support for tracking ToDos, Deadlines, and Events
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
Handle errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when the project starts up.
Store deadline and event dates as a java.time.LocalDate in the task objects. Accept dates in yyyy-mm-dd format and print in MMM dd yyyy format
Extract Ui, Storage, Parser, TaskList, and Command into Classes
Organize the classes into suitable java packages.
Use Gradle to automate some of the build tasks of the project.
Add JUnit tests to test the behavior of the code.
Add JavaDoc comments to the code.
Tweak the code to comply with a given coding standard
Give users a way to find a task by searching for a keyword
Use checkStyle to detect coding style violations
Add a GUI to Duke with JavaFX technology

Use assert feature to document important assumptions that should hold at various points in the code There are no checks to ensure the correctness of each aspect of the program (e.g. variable values at certain points in time). It allows some bugs to be left undetected until an Exception happens and theprogram is terminated. Adding assertions into the program acts as a sanity check and helps in ensuring the correctness of the program.
Examines the code and refactor to improve the code quality where necessary
commitResults.messageBody:
Important exceptions were not thrown, causing the program to terminate when bugs occur.

Exceptions need to be thrown and catch to ensure the code works as intended and to eliminate bugs.

Important exceptions are thrown and catch, and the error message is displayed in Duke GUI, especially for exceptions regarding array out of bound and incorrect syntax.
